Fiat’s Turkish Unit Agrees to Export Minivans in U.S., Canada

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-09-11T11:21:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-11/fiat-s-turkish-unit-agrees-to-export-minivans-in-u-s-canada.html
Tofas Turk Otomobil Fabrikasi AS (TOASO) ,
the automaker owned by  Fiat SpA (F)  and Turkey’s  Koc Holding AS (KCHOL) ,
will export 190,000 units of its Doblo minivans with Chrysler
Group LLC to the U.S. and Canada starting in 2013.  Tofas will invest $160 million to increase capacity of
Doblo’s production as part of the seven-year agreement, the
company said in a statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange 
today. The Doblo minivans will be sold under Chrysler’s Ram
brand, according to the statement.  Turkey, which has no automotive brands of its own, is a
production hub for Hyundai Motor Co., Toyota Motor Corp. and
 Renault SA. (RNO)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
